ase\", \"from\": 145, \"to\": 153}, {\"ngram\": \"your browser\", \"from\": 162, \"to\": 174}, {\"ngram\": \"Swipe\", \"from\": 191, \"to\": 196}, {\"ngram\": \"next article\", \"from\": 201, \"to\": 213}, {\"ngram\": \"The seven-time champion\", \"from\": 214, \"to\": 237}, {\"ngram\": \"bookmarks\", \"from\": 324, \"to\": 333}, {\"ngram\": \"offers\", \"from\": 367, \"to\": 373}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 375, \"to\": 381}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 386, \"to\": 393}, {\"ngram\": \"The Independent\", \"from\": 399, \"to\": 414}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice Hannah Cockroftis backing Britain's wheelchair racers to clinch a stunning \\\"clean sweep\\\" at the Paris Paralympic Games.\", \"from\": 420, \"to\": 563, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 470, \"end\": 477, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9975979680201823, \"rank\": 0.002406116399272854, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 425, \"to\": 442}, {\"ngram\": \"Hannah Cockroftis\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 460}, {\"ngram\": \"a stunning \\\"clean sweep\", \"from\": 507, \"to\": 530}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Paralympic Games\", \"from\": 535, \"to\": 561}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The seven-time champion from Halifax will be looking to defend her T34 100m for the third Games in a row but faces stiff competition from Kare Adenegan, the only athlete to ever beat her on the international stage.\", \"from\": 565, \"to\": 779, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 594, \"end\": 601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Halifax_Panthers\", \"score\": 0.7573079726190868, \"rank\": 0.32046675349484693, \"text\": \"Halifax\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Halifax_Panthers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Halifax_Panthers\"}, {\"begin\": 632, \"e